# Entire runtime staging dir: build outputs, CMake-generated machine-specific
# cfgs, crash dumps, profiling CSVs, screenshots, runtime state. None of it is
# a source of truth (the cfg template lives in src/cmake/config/). Supersedes
# the old stage/shader-cache/ rule.
#
# EXCEPTION (2026-06-11): stage/override/ IS a source of truth -- the loose
# shader-override payload (//hlsl VS reauthors of //asm assets, PSRC-swapped
# .psh IFFs for the texren/emissive families) that the D3D11 renderer depends
# on via client.cfg searchPath_00_10. `stage/*` + negation (a bare `stage/`
# dir-exclusion would prevent git from descending into the negated child).
stage/*
!stage/override/

# ============================================================
# Phase 11+ runtime / harness / tooling cruft (added 2026-05-21)
# ============================================================

# Per-iteration build logs (the .txt convention; .log already globally ignored)
build-log-*.txt

# Automated crash dump pairs (.mdmp binary + .txt symbol dump) -- generated
# by the engine's fatal handler; can land at repo root or inside stage/.
SwgClient_d.exe-unknown.*

# MSBuild incremental tracker state for the build/win32 solution-level targets
src/build/win32/_all_*.tlog/
src/build/win32/_all_*.recipe

# Claude Code harness state (slash-command cache, settings, etc.)
.claude/

# Node tool install picked up by an unrelated tool; not part of the engine build
node_modules/
package.json
package-lock.json

# Planning subsystem runtime state (the .md docs under .planning/ stay tracked)
.planning/config.json
.planning/debug/